quran[49]{c,v,t}:
  43,57,"When the example of the son of Mary was given, your people laughed and jeered"
  43,58,"and they said, “Are Our gods better or he?” They only mentioned him to you for the sake of argument. They are indeed a contentious people"
  43,59,He was only a slave whom We favored and made him an example for the Children of Israel
  43,60,"If We willed, We could [destroy you and] replace you with angels, succeeding one another on earth"
  43,61,"And he [Jesus] will be a sign of the Hour; so do not have doubt about it and follow me. This is a straight path"
  43,62,"Do not let Satan turn you away [from the straight path], for he is your sworn enemy"
  43,63,"When Jesus came with clear signs, he said, “I have come to you with wisdom, and to clarify to you some of that concerning which you differ; so fear Allah and obey me"
  43,64,"Indeed, Allah is my Lord and your Lord; so worship Him. This is a straight path.”"
  43,65,"But the factions differed among themselves [about Jesus]; so woe to the wrongdoers from the punishment of a painful Day"
  43,66,Are they waiting except for the Hour to come upon them by surprise when they least expect it
  43,67,"On that Day, close friends will become enemies to one another, except the righteous"
  43,68,"[It will be said to them], “O My slaves, there is no fear for you Today, nor will you grieve"
  43,69,"[those] who believed in Our verses and submitted [to Us as Muslims]"
  43,70,"Enter Paradise, you and your spouses, rejoicing in bliss.”"
  43,71,"Golden trays and cups will be passed around among them; there will be all that souls desire and eyes delight in, and you will abide therein forever"
  43,72,That is Paradise which you will inherit for what you used to do
  43,73,You will have therein abundant fruit to eat from
  43,74,"Indeed, the wicked will be in the punishment of Hell forever"
  43,75,"It will not be lightened for them, and they will remain therein in utter despair"
  43,76,"We did not wrong them, but they themselves were the wrongdoers"
  43,77,"They will cry out, “O Mālik, let your Lord put an end to us!” He will say, “You are here to stay.”"
  43,78,"We surely brought you the truth, but most of you were averse to the truth"
  43,79,Have they devised a plan? We too have devised a plan
  43,80,"Do they think that We do not hear their secret talks and private counsels? Yes indeed, and Our angel-messengers are with them recording everything"
  43,81,"Say, “If the Most Compassionate truly had a son, I would be the first of [his] worshipers.”"
  43,82,"Glory be to the Lord of the heavens and earth, Lord of the Throne, far above what they ascribe [to Him]"
  43,83,So leave them to indulge in falsehood and amuse themselves until they meet their Day that they are promised
  43,84,"It is He Who is God in the heaven and God on earth, and He is the All-Wise, the All-Knowing"
  43,85,"Blessed is He to Whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and earth and all that is between them. With Him is the knowledge of the Hour, and to Him you will be returned"
  43,86,"Those whom they supplicate besides Him have no power to intercede, except those who testify to the truth on the basis of knowledge"
  43,87,"If you ask them who created them, they will surely say, “Allah.” How are they then deluded"
  43,88,"[The Prophet] said: “O my Lord, indeed, these are a people who do not believe.”"
  43,89,"So turn away from them and say, “Peace.” They will come to know"
  44,1,Hā Mīm
  44,2,By the clear Book
  44,3,"Indeed, We sent it down on a blessed night, for We give warning"
  44,4,"On that night, every matter of wisdom is determined"
  44,5,by Our command. We have always sent messengers
  44,6,"as a mercy from your Lord. He is indeed the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing"
  44,7,"Lord of the heavens and earth and all that is between them, if only you had sure faith"
  44,8,"None has the right to be worshiped except Him, Who gives life and causes death – your Lord, and the Lord of your forefathers"
  44,9,"But they are in doubt, amusing themselves"
  44,10,So wait for a day when the sky will bring forth a visible smoke
  44,11,that will overwhelm the people. This is a painful punishment
  44,12,"[They will cry,] “Our Lord, remove the punishment from us; we will surely believe!”"
  44,13,"How will they take heed, when a messenger who explained things clearly has already come to them"
  44,14,"Then they turned away from him and said, “[He is] a madman, taught by others.”"
  44,15,"We shall hold the punishment back for a while, but you will surely return [to disbelief]"
  44,16,"On the Day when We seize [them] with the greatest assault, We will surely exact retribution"